g annotationType with getMethod, the specified method must exist. This gives me a lot to consider about how I structure the interface properly!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting annotation types**\\n\\nI realize that the visitor skips `java.lang.annotation` annotations at the top level when using `visitAnnotation`, but the `RecursiveAnnotationArrayVisitor` only requires the `annotationType` method. I can instantiate `AnnotationAttributes` for any annotation type name through `AnnotationMetadataReadingVisitor`. It seems like the top-level visitor bypasses the `java.lang.annotation` package but not `java.lang`. I might consider using an annotation type from the Spring library that has public array attributes. I'll need to check examples, like `org.springframework.core.annotation.AliasFor`, which has `String[]`. Let's investigate!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_MTXHfjLTqQcyVSEKyNMXv7Sp|fc_0f21ea1f5ab8ae430169f596343b3c81a2b42c006297a367b6", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"public @interface|@interface|\\[\\]\" /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge8/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/main/extracted/org/springframework -S | head -100", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 563, "output": 1235, "cacheRead": 25088, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26886, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777702430512, "responseId": "resp_0f21ea1f5ab8ae430169f5961ef6b481a2921ff0ba13235300"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_MTXHfjLTqQcyVSEKyNMXv7Sp|fc_0f21ea1f5ab8ae430169f596343b3c81a2b42c006297a367b6", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge8/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/main/extrac