[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering annotation options**\n\nI’m exploring using an annotation type from the org.springframework package to address a filter. It seems there isn't an array annotation in spring-core. I’m pondering if I should create a test annotation under org.springframework, but the rule says not to keep tests inside library packages. Maybe helper test annotations could go in org_springframework only, but creating a class in that package seems off. Hm, could I use a JDK annotation instead? The reflection config for JDK shouldn’t be an issue.\n\n**Identifying potential issues**\n\nI’m noticing a couple of potential issues regarding generated annotations. For instance, in the class file, if an empty array entry for an annotation type exists, it can be encoded without specifying the element type. The visitor doesn't know the array type from the bytecode and only uses getMethod during visitEnd. I'm also considering issues around class constructors and annotation visibility. What happens if a metadata reading visitor overlooks an annotation due to visibility? It's a complex situation!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0f21ea1f5ab8ae430169f5965f844881a2a78f04dee2a6dc99\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9ZZvSwfgyb4WSRbOqPyoRUdQXFxE3LBbiLIeegGTxyf2YTDDJX75wcSpeUtZ6rFyBKC5LpBpBRSsZ0T0sils2PfwS3CYL4p8fYBrq0au9BSI9JDrHOksYSXGofsPumtWW1XHNMTCxyz4Pf4EbgccKQmP45bncq3r5wWm7ywv74k7V8GFMZdtxLNFPaICK-b6jEOcS8XpxB03-i8-oxEtJU1SW0yrsD2VC4qYlNGDlvQKhbMVCcFlCArjy3foqjkkdfJfJgeHcs2XM47ORbQRNWFqtHfmh36a6gd1AAhC6md7IyiGAg2kchudd05-RezCpRvgQckZG--MTwcNFfKGY3G3ea35UTrUjTyV9OH1e8pWFlOuwvdIcqi6J-wkJRv2XMI6M5Aer90DnW-L9juIQgKkCsjpCZYQ3UrzaxAql0rjYlh1UoQ2Zpvm36VvOgaSFtkz0fDec65_clkNg98ZXCfIzC33LK6VbJTGx89NgTbjnJwyw1Xbq4TZ52R8ftWrtZmdekTrGBLANH2xBcIXjSBExv2i-ikVXtpr8-UjcWFoDTw_fIR9l9MDvohancXzFQRZliW_1lsObucTWJG1AVyhIisWNZtMnlnEbrNgVvKF0vCF5I6FyauefdKUUBobQiSSnptxak0zzPoP6